<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-720-832  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 720 832.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>LAN Magazine  August 1990 v5 n8 p10(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Telecon Library Inc. 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Earnings roundup.andM;</TITLE><DESCRIPT>Topic:     ProfitCompaniesComputer Industry.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>EARNINGS ROUNDUPandM;Novell (Provo, Utah) has reported a significant earnings increase for itssecond quarter.andP;  For the three-month period ending April 28, Novell reporteda net income of $20.5 million, up 78 percent from the $11.5 million postedfor the same quarter last year.andP;  Per-share profits were up 71 percent, to 60cents from 35 cents.andP;  Net revenue for the period was $120 million, up 9percent from $110.4 million last year.andM;The profit figures include expenses of $400,000 related to Novell's failedmerger attempt with Lotus; Novell says additional merger costs will alsoimpact the company's third-quarter performance.andM;Novell president and CEO Ray Noorda attributed the strong profit figures to&quot;continuation of our systems software strategy and the importance we place onmanaging the fundamentals of our business.&quot;andM;Network General (Menlo Park, Calif.) has reported record fourth-quarterrevenue of $8.8 million, an increase of 119 percent over the $4.0 milliontabulated for a year ago.andP;  The firm had net income of $1.7 million (24cents), up 118 percent, versus $784,000 (14 cents) a year ago.andM;For the fiscal year ending March 31, Network General's revenues were $29.4million, 129 percent more than the $12.9 million of 1989.andP;  Net income for theyear was up 131 percent to $5.9 million (86 cents), compared to $2.6 million(51 cents) last year.andM;Businessland (San Jose, Calif.) has reported sales of $323.4 million for thethird quarter ending March 31, which represents a 10 percent gain over the$293.3 million sales recorded for the same period a year ago.andP;  Earnings of$186,000 for the company's consolidated operations were in line withprojections released April 5.andM;However, Businessland still reported an overall loss of $1.7 million (6 centsper share) as a result of interest expenses on outstanding loans.andP;  Thiscompares with the net income of $8.5 million last year.andO;</TEXT></DOC>